contentrichtext.text: <!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------> <!-- MoS:Disambiguation - prefer ONE LINK per entry, short descriptions. --> <!-- Avoid piping, external links, and red links with little article potential --> <!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------> '''Gulliver''' can refer to: In '''fiction''': *[[Lemuel Gulliver]], the main character of the story ''[[Gulliver's Travels]]'' by Jonathan Swift *Gulliver "Gully" Foyle, the lead protagonist in the science fiction novel ''[[The Stars My Destination]]'' *In the novel ''[[A Clockwork Orange]]'', [[Nadsat]] slang for "head" *Gulliver, a raven in the story ''[[Benjamin the Elephant]]'' * [[Gulliver's Travels (2010 film)]], fantasy comedy film '''Other''': *[[Gulliver, Queensland]], a suburb of Townsville in Australia *Gulliver, an impact crater on the Martian moon [[Phobos (moon)|Phobos]] *[[Dorothy Gulliver]], an actress *[[Isaac Gulliver]], a smuggler *[[Phil Gulliver]], a footballer *[[Trina Gulliver]], a darts player *[[Gulliver Preparatory School]], a preparatory school in Miami, Florida *Lake Gulliver, a lake in [[Michigan]], USA *[[Gulliver, Michigan]], a city on the shores of the above *Gulliver, the largest wind turbine in the U.K. at [[Ness Point]] in [[Lowestoft]] *[[Gullivers Cove, Nova Scotia]] * [[Gulliver (building)]], a 35-storey mixed-use building currently under construction in Kiev, Ukraine * ''The Gulliver'', an airplane used by [[Wendell Willkie]] in worldwide travels during the 1940's {{disambig}}
